      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument for border security is morally defensible because it prioritizes the safety and sovereignty of the nation's citizens, who have a right to live in peace without fear of predation or exploitation by uncontrolled entry. Conversely, the argument for humanitarian asylum is morally defensible because it upholds the fundamental human right to seek refuge from persecution, hunger, and war, as seen in the historical precedents of nations like the US and Germany. Ultimately, which side is \"more\" defensible depends on whether one believes the primary moral duty is to protect the existing community or to fulfill a global obligation to the vulnerable.",
